tinyxml
------------------------------------------
TinyXML is a simple, small, C++ XML parser that can be easily integrating into
other programs.

I found myself writing a text file parser every time I needed to save human
readable data or serialize objects; I created TinyXML to solve the text I/O
file once and for all. (Or, as a friend said, end the Just Another Text File
Parser problem.)

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.33-1
  libgcc1-4.9.2-1
  libstdc++6-4.9.2-1
  libtinyxml-devel-2.6.2-1bl2
  libtinyxml0-2.6.2-1bl2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.24.51-6
  cygport-0.17.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-1
  libtool-2.4.2-5
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.grinninglizard.com/tinyxml/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/tinyxml/tinyxml_2_6_2.zip

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack tinyxml-2.6.2-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./tinyxml-2.6.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/tinyxml-2.6.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/tinyxml-2.6.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtinyxml0-2.6.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtinyxml-devel-2.6.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(tinyxml)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/tinyxml.README
  /usr/share/doc/tinyxml/CHANGES.txt
  /usr/share/doc/tinyxml/readme.txt

(libtinyxml0)
  /usr/bin/cygtinyxml-0.dll

(libtinyxml-devel)
  /usr/include/tinyxml.h
  /usr/lib/libtinyxml.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/tinyxml.pc

